content.description: This problem is a traverse that starts on the over hanging east side of the boulder to the right of Finn It. Start with matching hands on low rail in the middle of the east side of the boulder. Move up to higher rail and start moving left. This problem traverses through Finn It and Jake the Dog. Traverse all the way to the left of Jake the Dog. Top out on the farthest left arete over the three smaller rocks at the bottom.
content.location: Starts to the right on Finn It on East side of boulder.

content.description: Start with matching hands on the low small half hueco. feet are on the nice rail on the bottom of boulder. Go straight up and top out.
content.location: When you first come across the boulder from the bike trail you will see the south side of the boulder. Jake the Dog is right in the middle.

content.description: Start low on with left hand on large sloping hold. Right hand is nice crimp to right. Feet are on the giant rail under the boulder. Go straight up and top out. The last move is the crux. It can be done dynamic or static with a high foot.
content.location: This problem is to The right of Jake the Dog its the right Arete.

content.description: Start on same rail as on the quest in the middle of the east side of the boulder. Move up to higher rail and top out. Problem to the right of Finn It.
content.location: East side of adventure Time Boulder Same start as the Quest to the right of Finn it

content.description: This boulder has lot of cool formations on it. The rock is shape so be careful. The problems on this boulder go from over hang starts to vertical top outs. The problems require big static moves or dynamic moves at one point or another.
